  49. ‌let rec sum_lengths acc seplen = function
  50.   | [] -> acc
  51.   | hd :: [] -> length hd + acc
  52.   | hd :: tl -> sum_lengths (ensure_ge (length hd + seplen + acc) acc) seplen tl

  54. ‌let rec unsafe_blits dst pos sep seplen = function
  55.     [] -> dst
  56.   | hd :: [] ->
  57.     unsafe_blit hd 0 dst pos (length hd); dst
  58.   | hd :: tl ->
  59.     unsafe_blit hd 0 dst pos (length hd);
  60.     unsafe_blit sep 0 dst (pos + length hd) seplen;
  61.     unsafe_blits dst (pos + length hd + seplen) sep seplen tl

  63. ‌let concat sep = function
  64.     [] -> ""
  65.   | l -> let seplen = length sep in bts @@
  66.           unsafe_blits
  67.             (B.create (sum_lengths 0 seplen l))
  68.             0 sep seplen l

  101. ‌let trim s =
  102.   if s = "" then s
  103.   else if is_space (unsafe_get s 0) || is_space (unsafe_get s (length s - 1))
  104.     then bts (B.trim (bos s))
  105.   else s

  107. ‌let escaped s =

  201. ‌let starts_with ~prefix s =
  202.   let len_s = length s
  203.   and len_pre = length prefix in
  204.   let rec aux i =
  205.     if i = len_pre then true
  206.     else if unsafe_get s i <> unsafe_get prefix i then false
  207.     else aux (i + 1)
  208.   in len_s >= len_pre && aux 0

  210. (* duplicated in bytes.ml *)
  211. ‌let ends_with ~suffix s =
  212.   let len_s = length s
  213.   and len_suf = length suffix in
  214.   let diff = len_s - len_suf in
  215.   let rec aux i =
  216.     if i = len_suf then true
  217.     else if unsafe_get s (diff + i) <> unsafe_get suffix i then false
  218.     else aux (i + 1)
  219.   in diff >= 0 && aux 0
